	<br>
	</div>

	<div ng-show = "ctrl.current === 1" class = "info animate-show 1" id = "about">
		<h2>About</h2>
		<p>Our website is designed for <a href = "url(www.rosiesplace.org)" target = "_blank">Rosie's Place</a>, a nonprofit that provides resources for poor and homeless women. One service that they provide is a food pantry, where guests can take home groceries for free.</p>
		<p>More than one hundred women come, vying for eighty spots. These women crowd into the dining hall, and when the Rosie's Place soup kitchen starts to prepare meals, these waiting women are moved to a small sitting room.</p>
		<p> Our system helps women sign up for appointments ahead of time, so that they will not have to wait around for several hours in hopes of landing a spot. This helps the women save time and the charity save space.</p>
		<em>Note: This splash page is intended to introduce graders and other individuals to this website; food pantry guests and website administrators have their own login portals (explore below)</em>
	</div>

	<div ng-show = "ctrl.current === 2" class = "info animate-show 2" id = "features">
		<h2>Features</h2>
		<h3>Simplicity</h3>
		<p>Many guests of Rosie's Place do not have personal technology; their only exposure to computer interfaces are kiosks, such as those found at a doctor's office or pharmacy. Our design emulates these kiosks for their comfort.</p>
		<h3>Relevancy</h3>
		<p>We worked closely with Rosie's Place to ensure that the website includes options, such as offering guests a premade bag of groceries, that are specific to their program. We also gave website administrators control over hours of operation and accounts so that they will be able to manage the site independently of our team.</p>
		<h3>Accessibility</h3>
		<p>We provide guests with instant translations to five different languages, catering to backgrounds from around the world.</p> 
		<h3>Responsiveness</h3>
		<p>Our website uses Angular.js to provide a single-page experience with no refreshing, to make sure the website is responsive, even with slow internet connections.</p>
	</div>

